but I feel rather awkward and embarrassed. 

13
00:01:13,980 --> 00:01:17,690
I'll leave first. 

14
00:01:17,690 --> 00:01:21,980
Keep your eyes closed until you hear the door. 

15
00:01:21,980 --> 00:01:23,340
I'll call you later. 

16
00:01:24,330 --> 00:01:27,860
What? What are you doing? You can't do this! 

17
00:01:27,860 --> 00:01:29,760
What do you mean by that? 

18
00:01:31,420 --> 00:01:34,620
Mom, how did you find me? 

19
00:01:34,620 --> 00:01:36,360
I came to beat the crap out of you. 

20
00:01:36,960 --> 00:01:39,710
Mom, I'm sorry. 

21
00:01:39,710 --> 00:01:41,260
Are you really? 

22
00:01:41,260 --> 00:01:43,380
Mom, he's done nothing wrong. 

23
00:01:43,380 --> 00:01:45,960
It's all because I got drunk. 

24
00:01:45,960 --> 00:01:47,660
Are you still drunk? 

25
00:01:48,290 --> 00:01:50,280
- Huh?
- What are you talking about? 

26
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:52,070
He? Who? 

27
00:01:54,190 --> 00:01:57,330
Huh? What? Why am I here? 

28
00:01:59,320 --> 00:02:01,610
Quit drinking so much! 

29
00:02:02,860 --> 00:02:06,630
How can you drink every night? 

30
00:02:06,630 --> 00:02:10,800
And why did you bother your brother instead of going to bed in your own room? 

31
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:14,130
And why did you try to kiss him? 

32
00:02:14,130 --> 00:02:15,380
Me? 

33
00:02:15,380 --> 00:02:19,100
You said something about a matchmaker and tried to kiss him. 

34
00:02:19,100 --> 00:02:21,540
You know what he did? 

35
00:02:21,540 --> 00:02:23,380
He slept in my room. 

36
00:02:23,380 --> 00:02:25,070
Thank god your dad's on a business trip. 

37
00:02:25,070 --> 00:02:26,780
He would have kicked you out! 

38
00:02:26,780 --> 00:02:28,940
What did you mean about the matchmaker? 

39
00:02:28,940 --> 00:02:31,840
I don't know. I blacked out. 

40
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:33,140
Nice going! 

41
00:02:33,140 --> 00:02:34,540
Ouch, that hurts. 

42
00:02:35,950 --> 00:02:38,710
I can't believe you quit your teaching job. 

43
00:02:38,710 --> 00:02:40,960
Help around the house, at least. 

44
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:46,930
Ugh, you wreak of alcohol! 

45
00:02:46,930 --> 00:02:49,240
Don't you feel embarrassed? 

46
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:51,800
Daebak said you had sewer breath. 

47
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:54,060
What? I don't have sewer breath! 

48
00:02:54,060 --> 00:02:56,490
You do! I can smell it from here! 

49
00:02:56,490 --> 00:02:58,200
Go and brush your teeth. 

50
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:03,280
Ugh! I washed this two days ago. 

51
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:07,560
What if people start talking about you? 

52
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:10,040
Who cares about what people say? 

53
00:03:10,040 --> 00:03:11,490
What? 

54
00:03:11,490 --> 00:03:13,570
I'm just having a bad year, okay? 

55
00:03:14,540 --> 00:03:16,120
Why that little... 

56
00:03:17,310 --> 00:03:18,480
Ugh! 

57
00:03:19,950 --> 00:03:21,830
I'm leaving. 

58
00:03:21,830 --> 00:03:24,310
There isn't much time left.
Study hard. 

59
00:03:24,310 --> 00:03:26,650
You don't need to tell Haebak that. 

60
00:03:26,650 --> 00:03:27,670
Are you okay? 

61
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:31,000
- I'm dying.
- Don't come to my room! 

62
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,470
You jerk! 

63
00:03:32,470 --> 00:03:35,930
I'm not going to fetch you soup. 

64
00:03:35,930 --> 00:03:36,830
Go get it yourself. 

65
00:03:36,830 --> 00:03:38,460
Remember what Bong said? 

66
00:03:38,460 --> 00:03:41,310
It's better to go wild when you're young. 

67
00:03:41,310 --> 00:03:42,840
The law of the total amount of wildness. 

68
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:44,830
Look after Jungji today. 

69
00:03:44,830 --> 00:03:49,720
She kept me up all night.
Come home earlier and make the dog noise. 

70
00:03:49,720 --> 00:03:51,230
Uncle, can you do it? 

71
00:03:51,230 --> 00:03:53,310
When I do it, she starts crying. 

72
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:00,320
I'd cry, too. 

73
00:04:01,140 --> 00:04:04,400
Why don't you have Subak take care of them? 

74
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:06,850
She can't do that now. 

75
00:04:06,850 --> 00:04:09,350
Why not? They're her kids. 

76
00:04:09,350 --> 00:04:15,320
I raised my kids and took care of my in laws during the war. 

77
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:17,630
People can't understand the mother in laws 

78
00:04:17,630 --> 00:04:20,920
who talk about the old days and nag their daughter in laws. 

79
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:23,020
Ask anybody on the street if you want. 

80
00:04:23,020 --> 00:04:25,680
Why would I ask people on the street? 

81
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:28,030
They'll get upset if I stopped them. 

82
00:04:28,030 --> 00:04:31,820
I'm going to watch how good you are to Daebak's wife. 

83
00:04:31,820 --> 00:04:34,630
Leave me out.
I won't put my wife through it. 

84
00:04:34,630 --> 00:04:35,990
I know how it feels. 

85
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:41,870
You haven't sent it yet? 

86
00:04:41,870 --> 00:04:43,760
But I've been waiting for it. 

87
00:04:44,620 --> 00:04:45,760
Okay. 

88
00:04:47,390 --> 00:04:49,350
Sunjeong, I'm sorry. 

89
00:04:49,350 --> 00:04:52,990
It'll arrive some time tomorrow. 

90
00:04:52,990 --> 00:04:55,210
Receive it, but don't open it. 

91
00:04:55,210 --> 00:04:57,480
What is it?
Why are you so concerned? 

92
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:58,890
It's a secret. 

93
00:05:18,440 --> 00:05:19,930
Oh, no... 

94
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:08,790
Aren't you writing?
You said you would! 

95
00:06:08,790 --> 00:06:11,520
I will! I will! 

96
00:06:35,050 --> 00:06:37,940
Hello. 

97
00:06:44,300 --> 00:06:46,610
This is my table. 

98
00:06:46,610 --> 00:06:49,080
I always sit here whenever I come here. 

99
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:51,080
How did you know? 

100
00:06:51,840 --> 00:06:54,250
It beckoned me. 

101
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:06,920
Careful, your mouth will split! 

102
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:08,280
Where are you coming from? 

103
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:09,970
I was looking for a job. 

104
00:07:09,970 --> 00:07:12,620
Goof-off got a job without me. 

105
00:07:12,620 --> 00:07:13,880
How about you? 

106
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:16,580
I couldn't take mom's nagging anymore. 

107
00:07:16,580 --> 00:07:18,770
I have to move out if I don't get published this year. 

108
00:07:18,770 --> 00:07:22,120
Get a two bedroom so I can tag along. 

109
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,200
Ugh! 

110
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:26,120
Gwangbak, buy me some skewered chicken. 

111
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:31,030
Oh, really?
That sounds like a lot of fun. 

112
00:07:31,030 --> 00:07:32,650
Tell me more. 

113
00:07:32,650 --> 00:07:36,090
I don't think it's all that interesting,
but I'm grateful you think so. 

114
00:07:36,090 --> 00:07:38,330
Do you still see those friends? 

115
00:07:38,330 --> 00:07:41,680
Yes. We drink soju every now and then. 

116
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:44,000
Oh, soju! 

117
00:07:44,730 --> 00:07:47,000
But I'm not much of a drinker. 

118
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,950
But that's no fun. 

119
00:07:48,950 --> 00:07:51,980
That's how you learn about life. 

120
00:07:51,980 --> 00:07:54,200
I'm not saying I can't drink at all. 

121
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:56,040
I take sips. 

122
00:07:57,860 --> 00:07:59,240
Excuse me. 

123
00:08:44,130 --> 00:08:49,080
I'd love to have a drink, but I have plans. 

124
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:50,380
That's too bad. I'd like to, too. 

125
00:08:50,380 --> 00:08:52,090
I wanted to continue this at a bar. 

126
00:08:52,090 --> 00:08:55,070
Oh, I love bars, too. 

127
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:58,190
Just a second. 

128
00:09:02,860 --> 00:09:04,200
Stay still. 

129
00:09:34,770 --> 00:09:36,390
Look what I found. 

130
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:56,740
Good for you, Hobak. 

131
00:09:56,740 --> 00:09:57,820
Good job. 

132
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:01,020
You've worked so hard, 

133
00:10:01,020 --> 00:10:03,020
and you finally bought your own place. 

134
00:10:04,170 --> 00:10:05,260
Yes, father. 

135
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:09,020
I finally bought my own house. 

136
00:10:09,560 --> 00:10:11,770
But Sedal doesn't know yet. 

137
00:10:11,770 --> 00:10:13,770
I'm telling you first. 

138
00:10:14,380 --> 00:10:16,520
I'm proud of you. 

139
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:24,300
I remember the first place you lived in. 

140
00:10:26,140 --> 00:10:30,360
It was your first visit after I had Sintong. 

141
00:10:31,490 --> 00:10:35,700
It was such an awful place that I didn't even have a housewarming party. 

142
00:10:36,740 --> 00:10:39,160
I walked into the basement floor,  

143
00:10:39,160 --> 00:10:41,170
1 bedroom apartment with no windows, 

144
00:10:42,550 --> 00:10:47,740
and you were lying there in the dark, all swollen right after giving birth... 

145
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:53,500
It's as if it was yesterday. 

146
00:10:55,620 --> 00:10:58,170
That was the first time I ever saw you cry. 

147
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,910
You didn't make a sound, 

148
00:11:01,910 --> 00:11:04,520
but I still remember 

149
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:07,140
how your shoulders shook. 

150
00:11:08,240 --> 00:11:10,660
I couldn't even pay for your college tuition, 

151
00:11:11,570 --> 00:11:17,910
and I couldn't even give you a decent wedding because of Subak and Don. 

152
00:11:20,260 --> 00:11:21,840
Whenever I think of you, 

153
00:11:23,140 --> 00:11:24,980
it hurts right here. 

154
00:11:26,530 --> 00:11:28,400
It's okay, father. 

155
00:11:28,830 --> 00:11:30,940
I'm rich now. 

156
00:11:31,550 --> 00:11:36,830
It's a 3 bedroom and 2 bathroom apartment. 

157
00:11:36,830 --> 00:11:39,810
I didn't finish college, but I'm a general manager, 

158
00:11:39,810 --> 00:11:42,540
so I'm doing pretty well. 

159
00:11:42,540 --> 00:11:45,000
Owning an apartment in Seoul is a big deal. 

160
00:11:46,210 --> 00:11:49,350
Father, I did well, didn't I? 

161
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:52,530
Of course, of course. 

162
00:11:52,530 --> 00:11:54,530
I'm very proud of you. 

163
00:11:56,870 --> 00:12:00,980
But I can't tell mom. 

164
00:12:01,890 --> 00:12:05,740
I feel like I've done something wrong. 

165
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:09,220
Don't think that. Be proud of yourself. 

166
00:12:11,180 --> 00:12:12,440
I will. 

167
00:12:12,980 --> 00:12:16,700
I'll tell mom and Subak later. 

168
00:12:17,950 --> 00:12:19,180
You do that. 

169
00:12:20,870 --> 00:12:22,000
Oh... 

170
00:12:22,210 --> 00:12:23,750
I feel so relieved now. 

171
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:28,940
You finally did it. 

172
00:13:10,580 --> 00:13:11,580
Thank you. 

173
00:13:11,580 --> 00:13:12,850
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye. 

174
00:13:12,850 --> 00:13:13,970
Okay. 

175
00:13:16,890 --> 00:13:18,240
Subak. 

176
00:13:21,070 --> 00:13:22,540
What are you doing here? 

177
00:13:23,270 --> 00:13:24,540
No reason. 

178
00:13:25,180 --> 00:13:27,080
Did you go grocery shopping? 

179
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:28,490
Are you buying furniture? 

180
00:13:29,180 --> 00:13:31,230
I was just looking around. 

181
00:13:31,230 --> 00:13:33,630
In case my boys need something later. 

182
00:13:34,750 --> 00:13:37,020
Are you hiding something from me? 

183
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:39,690
Of course not. 

184
00:13:39,690 --> 00:13:41,420
I have to get back to work. 

185
00:13:41,420 --> 00:13:43,210
It's my lunch break. 

186
00:13:43,210 --> 00:13:46,170
I'll drop by to clean your bathroom. 

187
00:13:46,170 --> 00:13:47,340
Bye, Subak. 

188
00:14:06,410 --> 00:14:07,640
No way. 

189
00:14:07,640 --> 00:14:10,730
I'm sure!
She bought an apartment. 

190
00:14:18,950 --> 00:14:20,030
Father. 

191
00:14:23,730 --> 00:14:25,240
Why are you here? 

192
00:14:26,820 --> 00:14:30,070
Why are you here so late? Huh? 

193
00:14:30,990 --> 00:14:32,750
Why are you telling at her? 

194
00:14:32,750 --> 00:14:34,840
She came to see her girls. 

195
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:36,720
I thought I made it clear. 

196
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:38,930
Don't let her come here. 

197
00:14:38,930 --> 00:14:40,680
You were here all day, weren't you? 

198
00:14:40,680 --> 00:14:43,120
She came just now. 

199
00:14:43,120 --> 00:14:45,650
Mother, when did she come? 

200
00:14:45,650 --> 00:14:46,450
I don't know. 

201
00:14:46,450 --> 00:14:49,460
She never says hi or goodbye. 

202
00:14:49,460 --> 00:14:53,790
Maybe she's been here since morning or yesterday, but I didn't see. 

203
00:14:53,790 --> 00:14:56,100
You saw her come just now! 

204
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:57,480
What do you mean, yesterday? 

205
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:59,480
I said I didn't see her come in. 

206
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:01,550
- Did you see?
- No. 

207
00:15:03,750 --> 00:15:06,520
Take your girls and go home. 

208
00:15:06,520 --> 00:15:08,810
Why aren't you taking care of your girls? 

209
00:15:08,810 --> 00:15:11,250
You can't raise kids there. 

210
00:15:11,250 --> 00:15:14,200
There's no sunlight,
and it's infested with roaches. 

211
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:16,260
You don't know what you're talking about. 

212
00:15:16,260 --> 00:15:17,830
Kill them. 

213
00:15:17,830 --> 00:15:19,410
Look at Hobak. 

214
00:15:19,410 --> 00:15:21,760
She's raising her boys, 

215
00:15:21,760 --> 00:15:24,420
killing all roaches and mice. 

216
00:15:24,420 --> 00:15:26,540
Learn from your little sister. 

217
00:15:26,540 --> 00:15:31,510
She couldn't finish college because of you, 

218
00:15:31,510 --> 00:15:34,220
but she worked really hard and now she's bought... 

219
00:15:34,930 --> 00:15:36,640
Don't tell them, father. 

220
00:15:37,570 --> 00:15:41,220
She bought an apartment, didn't she? 

221
00:15:41,220 --> 00:15:43,220
I'm not saying she did. 

222
00:15:44,100 --> 00:15:47,580
I'm saying she's working hard to buy one. 

223
00:15:47,580 --> 00:15:51,170
Hobak's not relying on her parents. 

224
00:15:51,170 --> 00:15:53,460
Haven't you learned anything from her? 

225
00:15:54,070 --> 00:15:56,600
Go home and stop coming here! 

226
00:16:02,300 --> 00:16:05,180
What's wrong with you! 

227
00:16:05,180 --> 00:16:08,620
Why would you tell at our poor daughter? 

228
00:16:08,620 --> 00:16:10,440
What he said was right. 

229
00:16:10,440 --> 00:16:13,500
Burying coal won't turn it into a diamond. 

230
00:16:14,930 --> 00:16:18,760
I can't believe my ears. 

231
00:16:18,760 --> 00:16:22,300
Subak's coal and Hobak's a diamond? 

232
00:16:23,230 --> 00:16:26,000
She's been suffering from depression! 

233
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:27,670
How could you yell at her? 

234
00:16:27,670 --> 00:16:29,760
In front of everyone? 

235
00:16:32,840 --> 00:16:34,870
You shouldn't have talked about coal. 

236
00:16:34,870 --> 00:16:36,690
Egh, hyo, hyo, hyo. 

237
00:16:37,160 --> 00:16:38,370
Come out. 

238
00:16:41,420 --> 00:16:44,450
Don't keep shaking your head like that. 

239
00:16:44,450 --> 00:16:46,330
You might hurt yourself. 

240
00:16:46,330 --> 00:16:48,560
Oh, how disrespectful! 

241
00:16:49,330 --> 00:16:51,340
You're treating me differently now that I'm working. 

242
00:16:51,340 --> 00:16:53,720
I actually felt like having some beer. 

243
00:16:53,720 --> 00:16:56,620
Pour your husband a glass. 

244
00:16:56,620 --> 00:16:58,620
How dare you! I'm older. 

245
00:16:59,220 --> 00:17:00,710
Me first. 

246
00:17:00,710 --> 00:17:02,220
I don't believe this! 

247
00:17:02,220 --> 00:17:04,680
This can only mean one thing. 

248
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:06,650
Sintong! Bangtong! 

249
00:17:06,650 --> 00:17:08,010
You'll wake them up! 

250
00:17:08,010 --> 00:17:09,590
I'm exhausted. 

251
00:17:09,590 --> 00:17:11,520
I won't touch you. 

252
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:15,000
I can't believe you're thinking about that. 

253
00:17:16,640 --> 00:17:17,850
Pour me some beer. 

254
00:17:18,460 --> 00:17:19,500
Yes, older woman. 

255
00:17:31,190 --> 00:17:32,340
Congratulate me. 

256
00:17:32,580 --> 00:17:33,640
Congratulate you? 

257
00:17:34,090 --> 00:17:36,080
Don't ask any questions. 

258
00:17:36,080 --> 00:17:38,830
Just say, "Congratulations." 

259
00:17:41,550 --> 00:17:43,740
I'm going nuts. 

260
00:17:43,740 --> 00:17:45,290
Why? 

261
00:17:45,290 --> 00:17:49,680
You have a knack for such things. 

262
00:17:49,680 --> 00:17:53,730
What? What do I have a knack for? 

263
00:17:53,730 --> 00:17:57,420
You got pregnant with Sintong on your own, 

264
00:17:57,420 --> 00:18:02,070
and you had Bangtong without talking to me. 

265
00:18:02,070 --> 00:18:05,880
And now you're pregnant with a third baby? 

266
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:08,970
Don't get ahead of yourself. 

267
00:18:08,970 --> 00:18:10,660
It's not a baby. 

268
00:18:11,090 --> 00:18:12,650
You're not pregnant? 

269
00:18:13,210 --> 00:18:16,520
Oh! Thank god. 

270
00:18:17,380 --> 00:18:19,370
Don't even think about it. 

271
00:18:19,370 --> 00:18:20,540
Look at the boys names. 

272
00:18:20,540 --> 00:18:22,270
Sintong and Bangtong. 

273
00:18:22,270 --> 00:18:23,870
What could we name the third child? 

274
00:18:23,870 --> 00:18:26,590
All I can think of is Ddongtong. 

275
00:18:26,590 --> 00:18:28,260
There are plenty of choices. 

