Three's enough.
One for you, one for us. 

554
00:36:10,170 --> 00:36:11,990
Mother, I'm sorry, 

555
00:36:11,990 --> 00:36:16,310
but the reason why I got a loan to buy this apartment was for the boys. 

556
00:36:16,310 --> 00:36:18,150
I want them to have their own rooms. 

557
00:36:18,150 --> 00:36:21,070
So you're leaving us behind? 

558
00:36:21,070 --> 00:36:24,400
Fine! You go off and live on your own! 

559
00:36:24,400 --> 00:36:25,820
Hobak, that's mean! 

560
00:36:25,820 --> 00:36:29,710
We stuck together through difficulties,
and now you're leaving us behind? 

561
00:36:29,710 --> 00:36:32,810
Mother, I'm sorry.
Later... 

562
00:36:32,810 --> 00:36:35,030
Later when?
When I'm dead? 

563
00:36:35,030 --> 00:36:40,610
You're not even sixty yet,
so living together won't be comfortable. 

564
00:36:40,610 --> 00:36:42,170
You shouldn't be that way. 

565
00:36:42,170 --> 00:36:44,960
You could at least ask us to come with you! 

566
00:36:45,850 --> 00:36:48,250
Well, mother... 

567
00:36:51,120 --> 00:36:52,510
Oh, boy... 

568
00:36:53,460 --> 00:36:54,860
What do we do? 

569
00:36:54,860 --> 00:36:56,160
I'll take care of it. 

570
00:36:56,160 --> 00:36:58,190
Sedal! Mom wants you to come over! 

571
00:37:01,440 --> 00:37:03,840
Ugh... You look disgustingly happy. 

572
00:37:03,840 --> 00:37:05,480
Close your mouth! 

573
00:37:05,480 --> 00:37:09,780
It's structurally impossible to close my mouth. 

574
00:37:09,780 --> 00:37:11,190
And that's why I drool. 

575
00:37:11,190 --> 00:37:13,350
You drool when you see women. 

576
00:37:13,350 --> 00:37:17,020
Talk to your wife and take us with you. 

577
00:37:17,020 --> 00:37:18,410
She won't listen to me. 

578
00:37:18,410 --> 00:37:20,330
You should convince her. 

579
00:37:20,330 --> 00:37:23,380
How can you leave your mom and sister here? 

580
00:37:23,380 --> 00:37:25,740
Right. And move into a nice apartment. 

581
00:37:26,620 --> 00:37:28,940
Sons are useless. 

582
00:37:28,940 --> 00:37:31,750
Buying an apartment isn't great at all. 

583
00:37:31,750 --> 00:37:33,370
I'll do my best. 

584
00:37:35,100 --> 00:37:36,440
Please! 

585
00:37:36,440 --> 00:37:38,280
You go and get married! 

586
00:37:50,910 --> 00:37:52,510
Parcel service! 

587
00:37:52,510 --> 00:37:54,390
Is anyone home? 

588
00:37:54,390 --> 00:37:55,920
It's parcel service! 

589
00:38:31,990 --> 00:38:33,010
Hello? 

590
00:38:33,910 --> 00:38:35,560
Parcel service. 

591
00:38:35,560 --> 00:38:37,260
Is anyone home? 

592
00:38:50,650 --> 00:38:52,660
Sir! Sir! 

593
00:38:58,800 --> 00:39:01,390
Hello? Is this 911? 

594
00:39:05,610 --> 00:39:07,670
- Good job.
- Thank you. 

595
00:39:07,670 --> 00:39:10,690
He's such a good person. 

596
00:39:27,780 --> 00:39:28,750
Father. 

597
00:39:30,370 --> 00:39:32,100
It's me, Minjung. 

598
00:39:32,100 --> 00:39:33,530
How are you? 

599
00:39:35,060 --> 00:39:38,200
I couldn't go see you during the holidays. 

600
00:39:38,200 --> 00:39:39,410
I'm sorry, father. 

601
00:39:39,410 --> 00:39:43,170
Everyone knows how busy parcel service people get around the holidays. 

602
00:39:44,040 --> 00:39:46,040
Is everyone doing okay? 

603
00:39:48,030 --> 00:39:50,590
You're not skipping meals, are you? 

604
00:39:51,950 --> 00:39:54,350
Don't worry about me. 

605
00:39:54,350 --> 00:39:56,620
I'm not working too hard. 

606
00:39:56,620 --> 00:39:58,800
I work when I get bored. 

607
00:40:00,470 --> 00:40:02,650
The fruits this year aren't very good. 

608
00:40:03,760 --> 00:40:07,110
How are Subak and the girls? 

609
00:40:08,170 --> 00:40:09,980
They're all good. 

610
00:40:11,040 --> 00:40:13,630
Don't work too hard, father. 

611
00:40:13,630 --> 00:40:16,880
And take good care of your health. 

612
00:40:16,880 --> 00:40:21,050
If anything happens,
call me day or night. 

613
00:40:21,770 --> 00:40:25,010
I'll drop by when things settle down. 

614
00:40:25,900 --> 00:40:27,300
Goodbye, father. 

615
00:40:45,350 --> 00:40:48,660
Parcel service.
Are you Mr. Park Jaesam? 

616
00:40:48,660 --> 00:40:51,020
I'll be there in ten minutes. 

617
00:40:51,020 --> 00:40:52,820
Okay. 

618
00:42:01,550 --> 00:42:03,690
Welcome.
Are you checking in? 

619
00:42:03,690 --> 00:42:04,690
This way... 

620
00:42:10,110 --> 00:42:11,590
You must be happy. 

621
00:42:11,590 --> 00:42:13,680
She asked for you.
Specifically. 

622
00:42:13,680 --> 00:42:15,460
It's room service. 

623
00:42:15,460 --> 00:42:16,910
Take it up. 

624
00:42:34,160 --> 00:42:35,820
Room service. 

625
00:42:35,820 --> 00:42:36,930
In here. 

626
00:42:40,840 --> 00:42:42,850
Room service. 

627
00:43:22,380 --> 00:43:23,800
What are you looking at? 

628
00:43:24,760 --> 00:43:26,220
I'm not looking. 

629
00:43:27,480 --> 00:43:28,890
It's okay. You can look. 

630
00:43:29,770 --> 00:43:31,330
Bring me a glass. 

631
00:43:31,960 --> 00:43:33,560
Yes, ma'am. 

632
00:43:54,680 --> 00:43:56,650
Where should I put it? 

633
00:43:57,690 --> 00:43:59,090
Over here. 

634
00:43:59,090 --> 00:44:01,090
- Excuse me?
- Right here. 

635
00:44:03,180 --> 00:44:04,280
Okay. 

636
00:44:40,740 --> 00:44:43,760
Why do you always do that when I'm around? 

637
00:44:43,760 --> 00:44:45,600
Are you doing this on purpose? 

638
00:44:45,600 --> 00:44:49,390
You think I wait for you to do this? 

639
00:44:49,390 --> 00:44:52,950
Unlike you, I'm a busy person. 

640
00:44:52,950 --> 00:44:56,110
As you can see, I'm a professional. 

641
00:44:56,110 --> 00:44:58,590
Ha! Professional my butt! 

642
00:44:58,590 --> 00:45:02,120
You lost all your customers to that new beauty salon. 

643
00:45:02,120 --> 00:45:03,200
What? 

644
00:45:03,200 --> 00:45:05,320
If you were good, you wouldn't lose customers. 

645
00:45:05,320 --> 00:45:07,090
What do you know about me? 

646
00:45:07,090 --> 00:45:11,570
I had a salon in Myeongdong when I was younger. 

647
00:45:11,570 --> 00:45:17,210
You wouldn't know because you were too busy cooking at home. 

648
00:45:17,210 --> 00:45:20,710
Anyway, I'm doing much better than you 

649
00:45:20,710 --> 00:45:23,290
who is busy raising your grandchildren. 

650
00:45:23,290 --> 00:45:27,370
Ha! I can't believe my ears. 

651
00:45:27,370 --> 00:45:29,080
I'm better off than you. 

652
00:45:29,080 --> 00:45:30,750
Don't get mad. 

653
00:45:30,750 --> 00:45:33,170
Anyway, congratulations. 

654
00:45:33,730 --> 00:45:34,570
About what? 

655
00:45:34,570 --> 00:45:39,200
Your second daughter's set for life. 

656
00:45:39,200 --> 00:45:43,660
You should've been nicer to Hobak instead of focusing on Subak. 

657
00:45:43,660 --> 00:45:45,660
Let's be honest here. 

658
00:45:45,660 --> 00:45:48,050
What have you done for her? 

659
00:45:48,050 --> 00:45:50,570
You're Mrs. Vice Principal, 

660
00:45:50,570 --> 00:45:56,390
and you let your daughter get married without any dowry. 

661
00:45:56,390 --> 00:46:00,800
Did you know that people talked behind your back about that? 

662
00:46:00,800 --> 00:46:02,320
I let it go because I'm a nice person. 

663
00:46:02,320 --> 00:46:03,700
Who said what? Who? 

664
00:46:03,700 --> 00:46:04,980
Which one was it? 

665
00:46:04,980 --> 00:46:07,180
Everyone talked about you. 

666
00:46:07,180 --> 00:46:09,040
You can go and ask. 

667
00:46:09,040 --> 00:46:11,380
Are you on drugs? 

668
00:46:11,380 --> 00:46:13,020
You seem determined. 

669
00:46:13,800 --> 00:46:16,610
You think I don't have anything to say? 

670
00:46:16,610 --> 00:46:22,340
She was carrying a child, and that should've been enough of dowry! 

671
00:46:22,340 --> 00:46:26,710
She gave birth to two healthy boys! 

672
00:46:26,710 --> 00:46:30,080
But she should've brought dowry. 

673
00:46:30,080 --> 00:46:33,500
You should be nicer when she moves this time. 

674
00:46:33,500 --> 00:46:37,020
Buy her a fridge or a TV. 

675
00:46:37,020 --> 00:46:39,120
I'm letting you know early. 

676
00:46:39,120 --> 00:46:40,630
Stop. 

677
00:46:40,630 --> 00:46:42,320
What are you talking about? 

678
00:46:42,320 --> 00:46:44,570
You don't understand Korean? 

679
00:46:44,570 --> 00:46:46,900
Your second daughter. 

680
00:46:46,900 --> 00:46:51,270
When she moves to the new apartment, buy her a gift. 

681
00:46:51,270 --> 00:46:53,990
Move? 

682
00:46:53,990 --> 00:46:55,790
You didn't know? 

683
00:46:55,790 --> 00:47:00,220
She bought an apartment across the street, 
and they're moving there next week. 

684
00:47:00,220 --> 00:47:03,340
You're her mother and you didn't know? 

685
00:47:12,180 --> 00:47:14,230
Why are you scared?
Did you commit a crime? 

686
00:47:14,230 --> 00:47:16,540
You bought it with the money you earned! 

687
00:47:16,540 --> 00:47:17,710
Brag about it. 

688
00:47:17,710 --> 00:47:19,900
Go to your mother's and brag about it. 

689
00:47:19,900 --> 00:47:21,040
Why are you sorry? 

690
00:47:21,040 --> 00:47:23,200
Is what happened to Subak your fault? 

691
00:47:32,240 --> 00:47:33,480
Grandmother. 

692
00:47:33,480 --> 00:47:35,480
Oh, hi. 

693
00:47:36,160 --> 00:47:37,760
Did you bring something? 

694
00:47:37,760 --> 00:47:39,080
Have a seat. 

695
00:47:40,910 --> 00:47:42,340
What's that? 

696
00:47:42,340 --> 00:47:44,610
Buns. They are for you and mom. 

697
00:47:46,250 --> 00:47:49,720
You always came empty handed before. 

698
00:47:50,150 --> 00:47:52,050
I can't believe you. 

699
00:47:52,720 --> 00:47:55,160
I wouldn't get upset over buying a house. 

700
00:47:55,160 --> 00:47:57,520
Why would you hide it?
How devious of you! 

701
00:47:57,520 --> 00:47:59,180
You bought an apartment? 

702
00:47:59,180 --> 00:48:00,240
Yes, grandmother. 

703
00:48:00,240 --> 00:48:01,720
Oh, wow. 

704
00:48:01,720 --> 00:48:04,460
How did you do that? Where? 

705
00:48:04,460 --> 00:48:06,620
The apartment across the street. 

706
00:48:06,620 --> 00:48:08,550
Oh, that place is expensive! 

707
00:48:08,550 --> 00:48:09,610
Hey, hey, hey, hey! 

708
00:48:09,610 --> 00:48:12,070
Hobak bought an apartment. Applaud! 

709
00:48:12,070 --> 00:48:13,180
- Oh, my!
- Oh! 

710
00:48:13,180 --> 00:48:14,410
Hobak, congratulations! 

711
00:48:14,410 --> 00:48:16,420
Wang Hobak, good for you. 

712
00:48:17,870 --> 00:48:20,250
Why do you look so sour? 

713
00:48:20,250 --> 00:48:21,760
Aren't you happy? 

714
00:48:21,760 --> 00:48:28,070
I'm too happy for words because I heard it from her mother in law. 

715
00:48:28,070 --> 00:48:30,540
She picked the moving date and bought new furniture, 

716
00:48:30,540 --> 00:48:33,260
but didn't say a word. 

717
00:48:33,800 --> 00:48:36,700
How could you let me hear it from that beauty salon woman? 

718
00:48:37,480 --> 00:48:39,400
I'm sorry, mom. 

719
00:48:39,400 --> 00:48:43,920
When Subak saw you walking out from the realtor's office with a contract, 

720
00:48:43,920 --> 00:48:45,440
you swore it wasn't true. 

721
00:48:45,440 --> 00:48:49,090
Did you think I'd steal it from you? 

722
00:48:49,570 --> 00:48:51,900
It wasn't that. I just felt bad. 

723
00:48:51,900 --> 00:48:53,760
So you know you should feel bad? 

724
00:48:53,760 --> 00:48:56,850
How could you do it at a time like this? 

725
00:48:56,850 --> 00:48:59,940
It's about time she bought an apartment. 

726
00:48:59,940 --> 00:49:01,150
I agree. 

727
00:49:01,150 --> 00:49:05,540
We should congratulate her, not scold her, don't you think? 

728
00:49:05,540 --> 00:49:07,560
You stay out of this. 

729
00:49:07,560 --> 00:49:09,280
You don't know what you're talking about. 

730
00:49:09,930 --> 00:49:12,940
I should've told you first. I'm sorry. 

731
00:49:12,940 --> 00:49:14,730
Don't be mad, mom. 

732
00:49:14,730 --> 00:49:16,490
I'm sorry. 

733
00:49:17,150 --> 00:49:20,200
I brought your favorite buns. Have some. 

734
00:49:20,200 --> 00:49:22,370
You eat them all! Crappy buns! 

735
00:49:30,930 --> 00:49:33,650
Right? She bought an apartment, right? 

736
00:49:33,650 --> 00:49:35,020
She's heartless. 

737
00:49:35,020 --> 00:49:37,020
It's like she's rubbing it in. 

738
00:49:39,920 --> 00:49:42,060
You really don't have any money? 

739
00:49:42,060 --> 00:49:44,510
Of course, I don't! 

740
00:49:44,510 --> 00:49:46,800
You don't have a secret stash put away? 

741
00:49:46,800 --> 00:49:48,210
What's that? 

742
00:49:49,310 --> 00:49:56,480
You've been married for long enough,
and you didn't secretly save any money? 

743
00:49:56,480 --> 00:49:58,540
Why would I do that? 

744
00:50:00,530 --> 00:50:04,230
That's how you help your mom out. 

745
00:50:04,790 --> 00:50:09,240
You didn't save any money behind your husband's back? 

746
00:50:09,240 --> 00:50:10,800
I don't have any such thing! 

747
00:50:10,800 --> 00:50:12,850
I would've used it if I had. 

748
00:50:12,850 --> 00:50:14,500
Why didn't you tell me this before? 

749
00:50:14,500 --> 00:50:16,720
I didn't know I could stash money. 

750
00:50:16,720 --> 00:50:18,990
And I never needed to do that. 

751
00:50:18,990 --> 00:50:21,650
I used what Minjung brought me. 

752
00:50:21,650 --> 00:50:23,620
Why would you hit me? 

753
00:50:23,620 --> 00:50:26,560
I'm just so frustrated! 

754
00:50:26,560 --> 00:50:29,550
You should've prepared for emergency. 

755
00:50:29,550 --> 00:50:31,900
I thought you had something. 

756
00:50:31,900 --> 00:50:34,760
I had no idea you'd be flat broke. 

757
00:50:34,760 --> 00:50:37,460
I can't believe you. 

758
00:50:37,460 --> 00:50:40,900
Talking to you is making me madder. 

759
00:50:40,900 --> 00:50:44,010
I'm already upset.
Don't add to that. 

760
00:50:44,680 --> 00:50:47,060
Give me back everything I gave you! 

761
00:50:47,060 --> 00:50:48,290
What? 

762
00:50:50,560 --> 00:50:52,100
Oh, boy... 

763
00:50:55,430 --> 00:50:57,220
Go inside.
I don't want to see you. 

764
00:50:57,220 --> 00:50:59,130
Ugh, I'm so frustrated. 

765
00:51:03,260 --> 00:51:04,230
Subak! 

766
00:51:04,880 --> 00:51:07,520
Oh, my! It is you! 

767
00:51:07,520 --> 00:51:09,520
I didn't think it was you. 

768
00:51:11,540 --> 00:51:13,920
So the rumors are true! 

769
00:51:14,870 --> 00:51:16,830
Is this your place? 

770
00:51:16,830 --> 00:51:19,710
No, I'm just visiting someone. 

771
00:51:19,710 --> 00:51:22,540
Don't be like that, Subak. 

772
00:51:23,470 --> 00:51:26,780
How could you live in a place like this? 

773
00:51:26,780 --> 00:51:29,290
There must be roaches here, right? 

774
00:51:29,290 --> 00:51:31,600
What are you doing here? 

775
00:51:31,600 --> 00:51:36,010
Oh, I had to collect money near here. 

776
00:51:36,010 --> 00:51:38,330
Uh, please keep this a secret. 

777
00:51:38,330 --> 00:51:40,490
Don't tell any of our friends. 

778
00:51:40,490 --> 00:51:41,850
Please. 

779
00:51:41,850 --> 00:51:45,120
Of course. I won't tell anyone. 

780
00:51:45,120 --> 00:51:51,020
Nobody would believe me if I told them that you're living in a place like this. 

781
00:51:52,380 --> 00:51:54,390
Oh! There you are! 

782
00:51:54,390 --> 00:51:57,200
You never answer your door! 

783
00:51:59,000 --> 00:51:59,880
Me? 

784
00:51:59,880 --> 00:52:02,030
You don't recognize me? 

785
00:52:02,030 --> 00:52:04,030
I'm your landlord. 

786
00:52:05,250 --> 00:52:07,800
I'm not good with faces. 

787
00:52:07,800 --> 00:52:08,940
Whatever! 

788
00:52:08,940 --> 00:52:10,870
Why aren't you cleaning the bathroom? 

789
00:52:10,870 --> 00:52:14,520
Didn't I tell you we must take turns? 

790
00:52:15,000 --> 00:52:17,070
But I don't use that bathroom. 

791
00:52:17,620 --> 00:52:19,410
What do you mean you don't use it? 

792
00:52:19,410 --> 00:52:21,070
Everyone must use the bathroom. 

793
00:52:21,070 --> 00:52:22,590
If you don't, you'll die. 

794
00:52:22,590 --> 00:52:25,590
I don't. I'm using a chamber pot. 

795
00:52:27,990 --> 00:52:30,410
Oh, you're using a chamber pot? 

796
00:52:30,910 --> 00:52:32,690
Oh, my... 

797
00:52:32,690 --> 00:52:37,960
Excuse me, she can't do that.
Can you leave her out? 

798
00:52:37,960 --> 00:52:41,620
She used to live in a huge apartment. 

799
00:52:41,620 --> 00:52:43,240
She was in the Miss Korea pageant. 

800
00:52:43,240 --> 00:52:44,250
Stop! 

801
00:52:44,250 --> 00:52:47,150
Who hasn't been in the Miss Korea pageant? 

802
00:52:47,150 --> 00:52:49,440
I was in it, too. 

803
00:52:49,440 --> 00:52:51,280
But I didn't pass the preliminaries. 

804
00:52:51,280 --> 00:52:53,640
Oh, she didn't either. 

805
00:52:53,640 --> 00:52:55,090
Stop! 

806
00:52:55,090 --> 00:52:58,420
You must follow the rules here. 

807
00:52:58,420 --> 00:52:59,540
Come with me! 

808
00:53:09,470 --> 00:53:11,260
Rub it clean! Clean! 

809
00:53:11,260 --> 00:53:13,360
Rub the corners, too! 

810
00:53:14,240 --> 00:53:16,020
You don't need to cover your nose! 

811
00:53:16,020 --> 00:53:18,330
It all came out from people's bellies. 

812
00:53:18,330 --> 00:53:20,330
Over here, rub here, too. 

813
00:53:20,330 --> 00:53:22,680
Oh, the people are awful. 

814
00:53:22,680 --> 00:53:24,770
Why can't they aim better? 

815
00:53:46,920 --> 00:53:48,710
It's parcel service.
I'll get it. 

816
00:53:48,710 --> 00:53:50,480
- I'll get it.
- Okay, Daese. 

817
00:53:54,200 --> 00:53:55,970
Why did you come so late? 

818
00:53:55,970 --> 00:53:58,290
I'm sorry. The traffic was really bad. 

819
00:53:58,290 --> 00:54:00,080
Here it is. 

820
00:54:00,080 --> 00:54:02,700
I stayed home because you were coming. 

821
00:54:02,700 --> 00:54:04,950
And you're two hours late. 

822
00:54:04,950 --> 00:54:07,170
This won't happen again. 

823
00:54:07,170 --> 00:54:09,600
I'm very sorry. Goodbye. 

824
00:54:18,090 --> 00:54:20,510
Let's see. 

825
00:54:42,630 --> 00:54:43,890
Uh, Sunjeong. 

826
00:54:44,280 --> 00:54:45,170
Come here. 

827
00:54:46,270 --> 00:54:47,760
Tada! 

828
00:54:47,760 --> 00:54:49,060
What do you think? 

829
00:54:49,060 --> 00:54:50,200
Do you like it? 

830
00:54:50,200 --> 00:54:51,480
It's pretty. 

831
00:54:52,020 --> 00:54:53,970
Here, it's for you. 

832
00:54:53,970 --> 00:54:56,390
Me? It's mine? 

833
00:54:56,390 --> 00:54:59,520
I bought it off the internet for you. 

834
00:54:59,520 --> 00:55:01,520
It's not my birthday... 

835
00:55:01,520 --> 00:55:03,300
Thank you, Daese. 

836
00:55:03,300 --> 00:55:05,640
I thought this would lift your spirits. 

837
00:55:06,640 --> 00:55:08,580
You didn't have to. 

838
00:55:17,940 --> 00:55:19,200
What? 

839
00:55:19,740 --> 00:55:21,550
I wanted to see the girls. 

840
00:55:21,550 --> 00:55:23,550
They went to bed. 

841
00:55:23,550 --> 00:55:24,760
Can I see them sleeping? 

842
00:55:24,760 --> 00:55:26,100
Why would you do that? 

843
00:55:26,100 --> 00:55:27,540
Putting them to bed was hard. 

844
00:55:27,540 --> 00:55:29,710
Don't wake them up. Just go. 

845
00:55:29,710 --> 00:55:31,930
Seeing them asleep won't change anything. 

846
00:55:32,890 --> 00:55:35,590
Aeji must be asking for me. 

847
00:55:35,590 --> 00:55:36,820
She's not. 

848
00:55:38,140 --> 00:55:41,410
Then please give these to... 

849
00:55:41,410 --> 00:55:42,960
Leave them there. 

850
00:55:44,130 --> 00:55:47,720
Do you know Subak has depression? 

851
00:55:51,050 --> 00:55:54,080
Don't walk around carrying cookies. 

852
00:55:54,080 --> 00:55:57,020
Try to make your wife feel better. 

853
00:55:57,020 --> 00:55:58,920
Hello, Minjung. 

854
00:55:58,920 --> 00:56:00,260
It's been a long time, Daebak. 

855
00:56:00,260 --> 00:56:02,400
Share these with Aeji. 

856
00:56:02,400 --> 00:56:03,460
Okay. 

857
00:56:03,830 --> 00:56:05,580
Aeji said she misses you. 

858
00:56:05,580 --> 00:56:07,130
She never said that! 

859
00:56:07,130 --> 00:56:08,650
Go to your room and study. 

860
00:56:08,650 --> 00:56:10,100
Go. 

861
00:56:11,500 --> 00:56:14,360
Good night, then. 

862
00:56:15,260 --> 00:56:18,510
So you want to see the girls? 

863
00:56:19,220 --> 00:56:20,320
Dad! 

864
00:56:20,320 --> 00:56:21,600
Yes, Aeji! 

865
00:56:22,660 --> 00:56:24,800
Aeji, I woke you up! 

866
00:56:24,800 --> 00:56:28,480
Dad, why didn't you come?
I missed you. 

867
00:56:28,480 --> 00:56:34,050
I missed you so much, too. 

868
00:56:34,050 --> 00:56:37,210
I will come every day to see you. 

869
00:56:37,210 --> 00:56:38,980
You woke her up? 

870
00:56:38,980 --> 00:56:40,520
Aeji, come here! 

871
00:56:41,880 --> 00:56:45,260
Grandma, I hate you!
I want dad! 

872
00:56:45,260 --> 00:56:47,370
What are you doing? Go! 

873
00:56:48,170 --> 00:56:48,840
I will. 

874
00:56:50,440 --> 00:56:51,370
Good night. 

875
00:56:52,390 --> 00:56:55,270
Aeji, I'll see you tomorrow. 

876
00:56:55,270 --> 00:56:56,970
I'll come back tomorrow. 

877
00:56:56,970 --> 00:56:59,570
Dad! 

878
00:56:59,570 --> 00:57:01,300
- Dad!
- No! 

879
00:57:02,050 --> 00:57:04,460
- Dad!
- No, Aeji. 

880
00:57:05,080 --> 00:57:07,290
- Dad!
- No! 

881
00:58:05,650 --> 00:58:06,960
I'm home. 

882
00:58:39,740 --> 00:58:41,080
We need to talk. 

883
00:58:43,810 --> 00:58:45,240
Get up. 

884
00:58:47,940 --> 00:58:50,470
What is it? I'm exhausted. 

885
00:58:51,160 --> 00:58:52,550
You're not cooking? 

886
00:58:52,550 --> 00:58:53,370
What? 

887
00:58:53,370 --> 00:58:55,920
Are you buying the rice and side dishes? 

888
00:58:55,920 --> 00:58:58,250
What's wrong with that?
They're delicious. 

889
00:58:58,250 --> 00:59:00,500
We're not out on a picnic. 

890
00:59:00,500 --> 00:59:02,150
How can you buy everything? 

891
00:59:02,150 --> 00:59:03,940
We won't save any money this way. 

892
00:59:04,680 --> 00:59:07,700
We should buy rice and make it ourselves. 

893
00:59:07,700 --> 00:59:09,560
The rice cooker will cook it for you. 

894
00:59:09,560 --> 00:59:11,660
How can you buy ready made food?

895
00:59:11,660 --> 00:59:12,980
But I don't know how to do it! 

896
00:59:12,980 --> 00:59:14,980
You can try. 

897
00:59:14,980 --> 00:59:17,450
I want you to cook dinner for me. 

898
00:59:17,450 --> 00:59:19,600
You're always talking about food! 

899
00:59:19,600 --> 00:59:22,530
I'm all stressed out, and you're complaining about food? 

900
00:59:22,530 --> 00:59:24,530
Who cares what we eat? 

901
00:59:24,530 --> 00:59:26,400
Why does it have to be cooked by me? 

902
00:59:26,400 --> 00:59:28,610
I'm not saying that. 

903
00:59:28,610 --> 00:59:31,720
At this rate, we won't be able to move out of here in 3 years. 

904
00:59:32,780 --> 00:59:34,770
You're saying it'll be my fault? 

905
00:59:34,770 --> 00:59:36,240
Let's try to save every penny. 

906
00:59:36,240 --> 00:59:38,100
Buying ready made food doesn't seem much, 

907
00:59:38,100 --> 00:59:40,200
but it's a waste of money.
We must save... 

908
00:59:40,200 --> 00:59:43,250
Don't tell me to save money!
You make more! 

909
00:59:46,320 --> 00:59:47,850
Why are you picking on me? 

910
00:59:47,850 --> 00:59:50,250
I'm already frustrated as I am! 

911
00:59:51,050 --> 00:59:52,780
Do you know how I feel? 

912
00:59:52,780 --> 00:59:56,890
I'm stuck in this room all day long! 

913
00:59:56,890 --> 00:59:59,570
Then go out and do something. 

914
00:59:59,570 --> 01:00:01,760
You're stressed out because you stay here. 

915
01:00:01,760 --> 01:00:04,380
I don't have any money to go out. 

916
01:00:04,380 --> 01:00:06,640
I was in the Miss Korea pageant. 

917
01:00:06,640 --> 01:00:09,260
How can I go out without money? 

918
01:00:09,260 --> 01:00:11,530
It takes money to go anywhere. 

919
01:00:11,530 --> 01:00:13,530
Why do you need money? 

920
01:00:13,530 --> 01:00:18,750
You can go to the park,
get fresh air and think about what to do. 

921
01:00:19,530 --> 01:00:22,520
What do you mean by that? 

922
01:00:22,520 --> 01:00:23,900
Do you want me to get a job? 

923
01:00:23,900 --> 01:00:25,370
I'm not saying that. 

924
01:00:25,370 --> 01:00:26,990
Be honest with me. 

925
01:00:26,990 --> 01:00:28,990
You would like me to make money, don't you? 

926
01:00:28,990 --> 01:00:31,990
Just say you want me to go out and get a job! 

927
01:00:31,990 --> 01:00:33,500
Fine! 

928
01:00:33,500 --> 01:00:36,120
Why can't you go and get a job? 

929
01:00:36,120 --> 01:00:39,510
I'd be grateful if you got a job! 

930
01:00:41,110 --> 01:00:43,360
That's what you really want, huh? 

931
01:00:43,360 --> 01:00:46,360
Now it's my turn to make money? 

932
01:00:46,360 --> 01:00:49,170
You're not getting what I'm saying! 

933
01:00:49,170 --> 01:00:52,090
A problem shared is a problem halved. 

934
01:00:52,090 --> 01:00:57,610
If you are frugal with money,
you'd be helping me out. 

935
01:00:58,730 --> 01:01:00,500
Do you want to live like this forever? 

936
01:01:01,220 --> 01:01:05,220
How much longer will you leave the kids with your mom? 

937
01:01:05,220 --> 01:01:07,220
Bring them right now. 

938
01:01:07,220 --> 01:01:08,550
No. 

939
01:01:08,550 --> 01:01:09,590
No? 

940
01:01:10,000 --> 01:01:12,140
How can I bring them at a time like this? 

941
01:01:12,140 --> 01:01:13,700
What do you mean by that? 

942
01:01:13,700 --> 01:01:15,510
You can't raise your own children? 

943
01:01:15,510 --> 01:01:17,050
We should raise your own children. 

944
01:01:17,050 --> 01:01:18,620
How can I raise them here? 

945
01:01:18,620 --> 01:01:21,260
There are roaches and mice! 

946
01:01:21,260 --> 01:01:23,600
How long will you keep them there? 

947
01:01:23,600 --> 01:01:24,960
I don't know!
I don't! 

948
01:01:24,960 --> 01:01:26,780
I don't want to hear anything. 

949
01:01:28,070 --> 01:01:30,650
Don't you miss the girls? 

950
01:01:30,650 --> 01:01:32,220
I don't miss them. 

951
01:01:32,220 --> 01:01:33,350
I'm sick of them. 

952
01:01:34,080 --> 01:01:35,350
You're sick of them? 

953
01:01:37,150 --> 01:01:38,840
You're sick of your own children? 

954
01:01:44,460 --> 01:01:48,030
I'm serious.
Bring them tomorrow. 

955
01:01:48,030 --> 01:01:50,430
No! I can't take care of them. 

956
01:01:50,430 --> 01:01:52,960
It's hard enough for me to stay sane. 

957
01:01:52,960 --> 01:01:53,910
What? 

958
01:01:55,410 --> 01:01:58,210
I can't take care of them.
I don't want to! 

959
01:01:58,210 --> 01:01:59,860
I regret it! 

960
01:02:01,630 --> 01:02:03,140
What did you say? 

961
01:02:03,920 --> 01:02:06,430
I said I regret it! Why? 

962
01:02:07,840 --> 01:02:09,000
Say that again. 

963
01:02:10,970 --> 01:02:12,620
What did you say? 

964
01:02:12,620 --> 01:02:16,980
I regret marrying you,
and I regret having the kids. Satisfied? 

965
01:02:21,650 --> 01:02:23,950
Why did you slap me? Why? 

966
01:02:23,950 --> 01:02:26,260
What did I do wrong? 

967
01:02:30,370 --> 01:02:54,870
Subtitles by KBS World 

968
01:02:55,560 --> 01:02:58,740
Do you still think of me first thing when you wake up? 

969
01:02:58,740 --> 01:03:01,240
No, not really. 

970
01:03:01,240 --> 01:03:03,620
What? Your wife got this job for you. 

971
01:03:03,620 --> 01:03:05,610
You can't fire me! I quit! 

972
01:03:05,610 --> 01:03:07,170
Did you? 

973
01:03:07,170 --> 01:03:10,150
Did you feel happy when I was struggling? 

974
01:03:10,150 --> 01:03:11,800
Get out! 

975
01:03:11,800 --> 01:03:13,070
I don't want to see you! 

976
01:03:13,070 --> 01:03:14,500
You're horrible! 

977
01:03:14,500 --> 01:03:15,900
Where's Subak? 

978
01:03:15,900 --> 01:03:17,590
I won't ever forgive her for this! 

979
01:03:17,590 --> 01:03:19,470
You won't forgive her? 

980
01:03:19,470 --> 01:03:21,100
How dare you say that? 

981
01:03:21,100 --> 01:03:25,210
Why do we have to tip toe around Subak and be accommodating to her? 

982
01:03:25,210 --> 01:03:27,450
Was Hobak adopted or something? 

